			<div class="content" id="post-content-4391372">
									

<p>The blue opposite text is one of the better format screws I’ve seen recently, but I didn’t find Jeremy Michaels to be a particularly interesting character. The way the interview is structured and Michaels talks feels designed to force a sympathetic response, either by rapidly building Michaels as a character or by getting the reader to relate to the article’s themes of emotional neediness and family ties. But it happens too fast and thus causes me to notice the artificiality of that character and the hasty injection of those themes.</p>

